To fix the empty print previews, I will update the global print styles in **`index.css`** and ensure the print command waits for the document to render in the modals.

**The Root Cause:**
The existing CSS rule `body * { visibility: hidden }` works correctly to hide content. However, the rule `#root > div:not(.print-force-container), .fixed { display: none !important; }` was too aggressive. It was completely removing the Modals (which have the `.fixed` class) from the DOM. Since the print templates are nested *inside* these modals, they were also being removed, resulting in a blank page.

**The Fix:**
1.  **`index.css`**: I will remove the aggressive `display: none` rules for `.fixed` and parent containers. Instead, I will rely on `visibility` handling and z-indexing to ensure only the print container is seen.
2.  **`QuoteDetailsModal.tsx` & `OrderDetailsModal.tsx`**: I will add a small timeout to `window.print()` to ensure the browser has fully painted the print template before opening the print dialog.

