To ensure that company details updated in the Settings Manager are immediately reflected in all documents without a reload, and to fix the "View Receipt" functionality (likely obscured by the navigation bar due to z-index issues), I am applying the following fixes:

1.  **`components/admin/SettingsManager.tsx`**: Updated the `handleSave` function to immediately write the new settings to `localStorage`. This ensures that when you generate a receipt right after saving, the `InvoiceTemplate` picks up the new data from the cache instantly.
2.  **`components/admin/SalesHistory.tsx`**: Increased the `z-index` of the View Receipt modal to `z-[110]` to ensure it appears *above* the fixed Navbar (which is `z-[100]`). This resolves the "does not function" (unclickable/hidden) issue.
3.  **`components/admin/InvoiceTemplate.tsx`**: Verified that it fetches from both cache and API to ensure the latest data is always displayed.

