To ensure you cannot sell products when the quantity is zero, I will implement strict stock validation on both the Frontend (POS Terminal) and the Backend (Sale Service).

1.  **Frontend (`components/admin/PosTerminal.tsx` & `types.ts`)**:
    *   Update the `Product` interface to include `quantity`.
    *   Update the POS search results to visually indicate "Out of Stock" items (red background, disabled).
    *   Prevent adding 0-quantity items to the cart.
    *   Enforce stock limits when increasing quantity in the cart.

2.  **Backend (`server/src/services/saleService.ts`)**:
    *   Modify `createSale` to strictly check if `stockEntry.quantity >= item.quantity` before processing.
    *   Throw a clear error ("Insufficient stock") if the cashier tries to force a sale, preventing negative inventory.

