To ensure that Receipts, Quotations, and Invoices all capture and display the **SKU**, **Part Name**, and at least one **OEM Number**, I am updating the respective creation logic and data fetching mechanisms across the system.

Here is the breakdown of the changes:

1.  **`server/src/services/saleService.ts`**: Ensures that when a Sale (Receipt) is created, the SKU and OEM numbers are saved into the `itemsSnapshot`.
2.  **`components/admin/PosTerminal.tsx`**: Ensures the POS sends SKU and OEM data during checkout.
3.  **`server/src/routes/order.routes.ts`**: Updates the Order fetch logic to include `oemNumbers` so that Invoices can display them.
4.  **`components/admin/OrderManager.tsx`**: Updates the Order transformation to include `oem` data for the invoice view.
5.  **`components/admin/QuoteManager.tsx`**: Updates the Quote creation logic to include `sku` and `oem` in the items list when selecting products.
6.  **`components/admin/InvoiceTemplate.tsx`**: Updates the template to render these fields for all document types (Receipts, Invoices, Quotes).

