To act as a Senior Backend Engineer and fulfill your requirements, I will implement a robust "Verify-Then-Print" workflow for M-Pesa payments on the POS.

Here is the technical breakdown of the changes:

1.  **Backend (MpesaService & Routes):**
    *   We already have `initiateStkPush`. I will ensure the `POST /api/mpesa/pay` endpoint returns the `checkoutRequestID` immediately so the frontend can track it.
    *   I will create a new endpoint `GET /api/mpesa/status/:checkoutRequestID` that allows the POS to poll for the payment status in real-time.
    *   The receipt generation logic in the POS will be gated behind this status check.

2.  **Frontend (POS Terminal):**
    *   I will update the `handleCompleteSale` function. When "M-Pesa" is selected, instead of instantly creating a `Sale` (completed transaction), it will first call a new `initiate-pos-payment` endpoint.
    *   It will then enter a `polling` state, checking the backend every 3 seconds to see if the user entered their PIN and the payment was successful.
    *   Only upon receiving `status: COMPLETED` from the backend will it finalize the sale and trigger the 80mm thermal printer.

